commit.message: Bump version number to re-publish on PyPI

Dropped tools dir from sdist

`wait_server` moved to test directory.

manifest includes new files too (pyproject, requirements, tox)
Fixed metadata for dev status and py3 support

Copyright year updated

ag -l Copyright | xargs sed -i \
    "s/\(.*copyright (C) [0-9]\+\)\(-[0-9]\+\)\?\(.*\)/\1-$(date +%Y)\3/I"
Added requirements file to run tests
Adding black as project check tool
Added copying file. Dropped legal boilerplate from files

Dropped .hgignore. Goodbye, Mercurial

No bad feeling, hg has been great, but I'm using git on all of the other
projects of mine, both private and at work, and when I've tried to go back on
hg I just couldn't find things, I've not been able to solve my problems and I
miss named branches too much.
Readme updated with the latest info.

Backed out changeset ab24ebbbfce2

The change made the module dependant on Psycopg 2.2.

gevent: use timeout=None to indicate no timeout instead of timeout=-1

the future versions of gevent will only allow timeout=-1. (0.12.2 and older allow both None and -1)
Using LOAD_FAST instead of LOAD_GLOBAL in the innermost loop.
